      • equals

        public <O> boolean equals(Object thisObj,
                          Object thatObj,
                          ParamList<O> paramList)
        Tests if two objects are the same given the info in the ParamList.
        First, tests equality of the two objects using ==. If they're equal that way, return true.
        Then, if either of the objects is null, return false.
        Then if neither object is an instance of the parentClass, return thisObj.equals(thatObj).
        If only one of the objects is an instance of the parentClass, return false.
        Otherwise, cast them both to the parentClass. Then get a list of all ParameterDescription objects that are to be included in an equals comparison. For each entry, call the getter on both objects and compare the results using Objects.equals(Object, Object). If they are all equal, return true. Otherwise, return false. As soon as one unequal parameter is found, the rest are skipped.
        Specified by:
        equals in interface ParamListService
        Type Parameters:
        O - the class of the object
        Parameters:
        thisObj - the first object in the comparison
        thatObj - the second object in the comparison
        paramList - the ParamList to operate on - cannot be null
        Returns:
        true if the objects are equal, false if not
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the parentClass, paramOrder, or paramDescriptionMap parameters are null

      • hashCode

        public <O> int hashCode(O thisObj,
                        ParamList<O> paramList)
        Creates a hashCode for an object given the info in the ParamList.
        Gets all ParamDescription entries that should be included in the hashCode. Then loops through them getting each parameter from the object. The results are converted to an array of objects and then provided to Objects.hash(Object...).

      • toString

        public <O> String toString(O thisObj,
                           ParamList<O> paramList,
                           Map<Class,Set<Integer>> seen)
        Creates a String representation of the provided object given the info in the ParamList.
        First, the class name String is retrieved using the ParamListServiceConfig.getClassNameGetter().
        Then, the hashCode is calculated using thisObj.hashCode(), and converted to a string using ParamListServiceConfig.getHashCodeToString().
        Then, the parameters String is created in a recursion-safe way.
        Lastly, ParamListServiceConfig.getToStringFormat() is used to create the final String. Arguments are provided to the ParamListServiceConfig.getToStringFormat() in this order: class name, hash code String, parameters String
        Specified by:
        toString in interface ParamListService
        Type Parameters:
        O - the class of the object
        Parameters:
        thisObj - the object to convert - cannot be null
        paramList - the ParamList to operate on - cannot be null
        seen - the map of classes to sets of hashCodes indicating objects that have already been converted to a string - if null, a new empty HashMap is used
        Returns:
        A String.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if thisObj, or paramList are null
